{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "MRI Volume",
  "description": "MRI Volume — an MRI slice selector and processor decomposed from the legacy MriVolumeGenerator.\n\nThree image-folder players (Axial / Sagittal / Coronal) feed a texture mux. Axis selection runs in two modes: a manual slider when Clip Trigger is off, or cyclic selection when Clip Trigger fires (stepping through axial, sagittal, coronal). The selected axis's texture goes through Sharpen (4-neighbor Laplacian unsharp mask), then Window/Level (a smoothstep contrast stretch: center and width map to the threshold range), and finally Invert intensity before reaching the output.\n\nThe layout separates axis control (mode selector, clip-based stepping, manual override) and window-level math (deriving the smoothstep bounds from center and width sliders) from the top-level flow, so the three volumes, mux, and processing chain read as a simple pipeline. The groups flatten to byte-identical behavior at load.",
